# Coding Conventions
- Use Python 3.11+ syntax.
- Follow existing patterns and project structure; don't reinvent what's already there.
- Prefer simple, understandable code instead of "clever" logic and workarounds. If you are unsure ask user for help.
- Avoid nested functions.
- Avoid hardcoding values, prefer parameters instead.
- Prefer vectorized operations over the loops.
- Avoid creating new files, prefer extending existing modules.

# Additional instructions
- Add inline comments for complex logics.
- Avoid doing multifile changes, work on one file at a time and verify work with user. Seek user approval before moving on.
- If available, use skills such as grill-me, grill-with-docs to understand better what user wants.

# Package management
- This project uses `uv` for package management.
  - Run scripts with `uv run python` not `python`.
  - Add and remove dependencies using `uv add` or `uv remove`.